        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>British Museum</placeName>
                    <date>7 February 1860</date>
                    <salute>My dear Henslow</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
                  <p>The ominous silence in M. <hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Laing’s letter as to the condition I annexed to the acceptance of the Trusteeship, pretend that it cannot be fulfilled. And indeed, on reflection, as it is a post-testamentary arrangement, I suppose the estate could not be charged with any expence that a Trustee might have to incur, or give any guarantee against contingent risks. I suppose, therefore, I must limit my trouble to the duties assigned to me by our good old friend, viz., the disposition of his pupils to the best scientific application.</p>
                  <p>Yours very sincerely, | Richard Owen.</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
        
      </body>
